@startuml
skinparam ComponentStyle rectangle
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #lightyellow

package "Physical Shop Floor (OPC UA Servers)" {
    [Laser Engraver OPC-UA] as LaserOPC
    [Delta Robot OPC-UA] as RobotOPC
}

package "Ingest Service (Python Worker)" {
    [OPC-UA Subscriber] as Sub
    [Data Processor] as Proc
    [Database Manager] as DB_Mgr
    [MQTT Manager] as MQTT_Mgr
}

database "TimescaleDB (PostgreSQL)" {
    folder "Telemetry Tables (Hypertables)" {
        [laser_data]
        [delta_robot_data]
    }
    folder "Event Tables (Standard SQL)" {
        [machine_events]
    }
    folder "CMMS Tables (Standard SQL)" {
        [cmms_data]
    }
}

node "MQTT Broker (Mosquitto)" as Broker

package "RESTful API (FastAPI)" {
    [API Routers / Endpoints] as API
}

package "Consumers / Clients" {
    [Grafana Dashboard] as Grafana
    [External CMMS System] as CMMS_Sys
}

LaserOPC --> Sub : Raw OPC-UA values
RobotOPC --> Sub
Sub --> Proc : Raw data (Any)
Proc --> DB_Mgr : Cleaned SensorData
Proc --> MQTT_Mgr : If hot_path == True

DB_Mgr --> [laser_data] : Numeric/Float (DOUBLE PRECISION)
DB_Mgr --> [delta_robot_data] : Numeric/Float (DOUBLE PRECISION)
DB_Mgr --> [machine_events] : Text/Strings (TEXT)

MQTT_Mgr --> Broker : MQTT Publish

Grafana --> API : HTTP GET (Retrieve data)
CMMS_Sys --> API : HTTP POST (Store OEE) / HTTP GET (Query OEE)

API --> [laser_data] : Read
API --> [delta_robot_data] : Read
API --> [machine_events] : Read
API --> [cmms_data] : Read & Write

note bottom of Grafana
  Grafana reads from the database 
  strictly via the FastAPI REST API 
  (no direct database bypass!).
end note
@enduml